<subSubSection id="620FF5FA7F305D4F48B252F4AB55ACDA" pageId="4" pageNumber="91" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="98A1C807B3DD129B7F593F6D5B674397" pageId="4" pageNumber="91">
<pageBreakToken id="BD5226C61AF21DFC7E1DEEBC9D9D9BDF" pageId="4" pageNumber="91" start="start">Remarks</pageBreakToken>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BEB55697BDB46AC01D23BEC744D4BA94" pageId="4" pageNumber="91">
This species was firstly reported in China (Wuyishan Nature Reserve, Fujian) by 
<bibRefCitation id="83AD46C87BF3B44A6127EBF18B834D02" author="Wang, JS" journalOrPublisher="China Science and Technology Press, Beijing" pageId="10" pageNumber="97" title="Fauna of Pyralidae of Wuyishan Nature Reserve in China." year="2003">Wang et al. (2003)</bibRefCitation>
. We reexamined their voucher material from Fujian (Ep704), which are in accordance with the original description of 
<taxonomicName id="0726381DC71FD87C562C5026435FD26B" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Stericta" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Stericta sinuosa" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinuosa">Stericta sinuosa</taxonomicName>
(Moore, 1888). The species was originally described in 
<taxonomicName id="0A5A5B4171C60BE1795379721B954DEE" genus="Scopocera" lsidName="Scopocera" pageId="4" pageNumber="91" rank="genus">Scopocera</taxonomicName>
(junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="2960A6DBC12423FF2BDBACEF11C768BD" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Stericta" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Stericta" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Stericta</taxonomicName>
). However, the species is closer to 
<taxonomicName id="0CF85C22142C9ADC116026F3CB7531AC" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Lista" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lista" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Lista</taxonomicName>
than 
<taxonomicName id="BCC6FA943861CC3207E916B8684E4744" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Stericta" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Stericta" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Stericta</taxonomicName>
, because it does not have hairs on the outer side of mid-leg tibiae and has quite different genitalia to those of 
<taxonomicName id="DDB6DE256FAB3ADAC76F12DBC9382A87" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Lista" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lista" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Lista</taxonomicName>
. Thus, a new genus is erected to place the species and a new species, 
<taxonomicName id="ED870ED39A80800944AB823615B71B68" genus="Ar." lsidName="Ar. apexiarcanusa" pageId="4" pageNumber="91" rank="species" species="apexiarcanusa">Ar. apexiarcanusa</taxonomicName>
Wang, Chen &amp; Wu, sp. n. In addition, the female is reported for the first time here.
</paragraph>
